.TH CLIP 1 "2026-04-17" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clip \- cross-platform clipboard bridge

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clip
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
\fIcommand\fR | \fBclip\fR
.br
.B clip
\fB--clear\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clip
reads from and writes to the system clipboard with identical behaviour on Windows, macOS, and Linux.
With no arguments and a terminal stdin, it pastes the clipboard to stdout.
With stdin redirected, it copies stdin to the clipboard.
Explicit \fB--copy\fR and \fB--paste\fR flags override autodetection.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-copy
Force copy mode regardless of stdin state.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-paste
Force paste mode regardless of stdin state.
.TP
.B \-\-clear
Empty the clipboard and exit.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-raw
Do not strip the trailing newline on paste.
.TP
.B \-\-primary
Target the X11/Wayland PRIMARY selection on Linux. Silently ignored elsewhere.
.TP
.B \-\-color " " \fIWHEN\fR
\fBauto\fR, \fBalways\fR, or \fBnever\fR. Respects \fBNO_COLOR\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-describe
Emit structured JSON for AI discoverability.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.

.SH NEWLINE HANDLING
Copy is byte-preserving. Paste strips exactly one trailing \fB\\n\fR or \fB\\r\\n\fR by default to match \fB$(...)\fR shell-substitution semantics. Pass \fB--raw\fR to disable the strip.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success. Empty clipboard on paste also returns 0 with empty stdout.
.TP
.B 125
Invalid flags, conflicting modes, or invalid UTF-8 input.
.TP
.B 126
Clipboard busy (Windows) or helper binary failed (Linux/macOS).
.TP
.B 127
No clipboard helper found on Linux (install \fBwl-clipboard\fR, \fBxclip\fR, or \fBxsel\fR).

.SH EXAMPLES
Paste:
.RS
.nf
clip
.fi
.RE

Copy:
.RS
.nf
echo hello | clip
.fi
.RE

Clear:
.RS
.nf
clip --clear
.fi
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B WAYLAND_DISPLAY
On Linux, if set, clip prefers \fBwl-copy\fR/\fBwl-paste\fR over X11 helpers.
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disables colour output (clip has no colour itself; flag accepted for suite consistency).

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pbcopy (1),
.BR pbpaste (1),
.BR xclip (1),
.BR xsel (1),
.BR wl-copy (1),
.BR wl-paste (1)
